  "prompt": "Why am I getting Likes from people in India when my ad campaign is targeted only to people in SF?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you're seeing Likes from people in India even when your ad campaign is targeted only to San Francisco:\n\n1. VPN usage: Some users might be using Virtual Private Networks (VPNs) that make it appear they're accessing from SF when they're actually in India.\n\n2. Location settings: Users might have incorrect location settings on their devices or social media profiles.\n\n3. Platform targeting limitations: Sometimes social media ad platforms aren't 100% precise in location targeting.\n\n4. Shared content: Your ad might have been shared by someone in SF to connections in India.\n\n5. Platform glitches: There could be a technical issue with the ad platform's targeting system.\n\nTo troubleshoot:\n- Double-check your ad targeting settings\n- Use more specific location targeting\n- Contact the platform's support\n- Review your ad analytics for more detailed location data\n\nWould you like me to help you investigate further?",
